section
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-8.offset-md-2.col-sm-12
        .text-center
          h3.mb-5.type--uppercase What is an M&A?
        p.lead.m32.pb32 Mergers and acquisitions (M&A) refers to the consolidation of companies or assets. A merger is the coming together of two companies to form one company. Acquisition is the buying of an existing company and where no new company is formed. In all M&A cases, two companies are involved where one company is offering to buy the whole company or only some of its assets.
section.pt240.pb240.imagebg
  .background-image-holder
    img.background-image alt="image" src=image_path('meeting-table.jpg')
section
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-8.offset-md-2.col-sm-12
        .text-center
          h3.mb-5.type--uppercase Why Excide?
        p.lead.m32.pb32 At Excide, we provide you with experienced VFOs that have gone through many M&A transactions. We will assist you in maximising your benefits through this new phase and keeping potential risks to a minimum through:

        ul.lead data-bullet="ti-check-box"
          li Strategizing deal terms
          li Deal Structuring
          li Planning the transaction process
          li Due Diligence
          li Integration Strategy

        p.lead.m32.pb32 After the M&A process, we will also assist you in the aftercare process where lots of planning is required for proper integration and to convert theoretical benefits contemplated to practical gains
